Sentencas: Thermogravimetry, phase formation, microstructural evolution, specific surface area, and electrical properties of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) cathode were studied as functions of its preparation technique.
Titulo: Enhancement of the interfacial polarization resistance of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathode by microwave-assisted combustion method

Sentencas: The pure perovskite LSCF cathode powder was synthesized through glycine nitrate process (GNP) using microwave heating technique.
Titulo: Enhancement of the interfacial polarization resistance of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathode by microwave-assisted combustion method

Sentencas: Compared with conventional heating technique, microwave heating allows the rapid combustion to occur simultaneously between the nitrates and glycine in a controllable manner.
Titulo: Enhancement of the interfacial polarization resistance of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathode by microwave-assisted combustion method

Sentencas: The resulting powder is a single-phase nanocrystallite with a mean particle size of 113 nm and a high specific surface area of 12.2 m(2)/g, after calcination at 800 degrees C. Impedance analysis indicates that microwave heating has significantly reduced the polarization resistance of LSCF cathode.
Titulo: Enhancement of the interfacial polarization resistance of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathode by microwave-assisted combustion method

Sentencas: The area specific resistance (ASR) value of 0.059 and 0.09712 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C and 750 degrees C, respectively, were observed.
Titulo: Enhancement of the interfacial polarization resistance of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathode by microwave-assisted combustion method

Sentencas: These values were twofold lower than the corresponding ASR of the cathode (0.133 and 0.25912 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C and 750 degrees C, respectively) prepared through conventional heating.
Titulo: Enhancement of the interfacial polarization resistance of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathode by microwave-assisted combustion method

Sentencas: Results suggest that the microwave heating GNP strongly contributes to the enhancement of the LSCF cathode performance for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Enhancement of the interfacial polarization resistance of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathode by microwave-assisted combustion method
